  "@type": "dcat:Dataset",
  "@id": "https://hantavirus.software/dataset",
  "dcterms:identifier": "https://hantavirus.software/dataset",
  "dcterms:title": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "HORIZON Hantavirus Surveillance Dataset"
  },
  "dcterms:description": {
    "@language": "en",
    "@value": "Open dataset of hantavirus outbreak case reports aggregated from 65+ authoritative sources: WHO, CDC, ECDC, PAHO, ProMED, THL Finland, national health ministries, wire services (Reuters, AP, AFP, BBC, EFE, Mercopress), peer-reviewed literature repositories (Europe PMC, bioRxiv, medRxiv, Crossref, arXiv), the Oxford Kraemer Lab individual-level MV Hondius ANDV line list (CC0, Dr Moritz Kraemer / Oxford, Sam Scarpino, Andrew Rambaut / Edinburgh-Nextstrain — 28-column per-person resolution, highest epidemiological granularity available for the 2026 outbreak), and the full Orthohantavirus NCBI RefSeq reference genome set (HantaNet, CDC Molecular Epidemiology and Bioinformatics Team, PMC10675615). Each record carries NATO Admiralty Scale (STANAG 2511) source qualification, Berkeley Protocol SHA-256 chain-of-custody hash, dual-confidence model, and Analysis of Competing Hypotheses (ACH) scoring. Ecological leading indicators include NOAA MEI.v2 ENSO and NASA MODIS MOD13A3 NDVI anomaly for five hantavirus-endemic regions. Covers all major Orthohantavirus serotypes (ANDV, SNV, PUUV, HTNV, SEOV, DOBV) globally from 1993 to present."
  },
